1
00:00:36,406 --> 00:00:37,824
Je-sun.

2
00:00:40,451 --> 00:00:41,494
Wait a minute.

3
00:00:41,869 --> 00:00:44,497
- Je-sun.
- I'll pretend I didn't hear you.

4
00:00:45,415 --> 00:00:46,958
Just go. Please.

5
00:01:16,362 --> 00:01:19,031
You must get the package before he does.

6
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:29,584
Je-sun!

7
00:01:30,710 --> 00:01:31,961
Je-sun!

8
00:01:39,218 --> 00:01:40,845
EPISODE 9

9
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:43,806
Are you okay? You're not hurt?

10
00:01:45,141 --> 00:01:48,060
What... what are you doing here?

11
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:52,607
How... how did you get here?

12
00:01:54,317 --> 00:01:55,318
Director.

13
00:01:55,943 --> 00:01:58,362
Director, please open your eyes!

14
00:02:00,573 --> 00:02:02,366
Oh, Director!

15
00:02:05,244 --> 00:02:06,579
Director!

16
00:02:09,916 --> 00:02:11,042
Director!

17
00:02:11,709 --> 00:02:13,335
- She's not badly hurt.
- All right.

18
00:02:13,336 --> 00:02:14,921
- Let's get her out of here.
- Okay.

19
00:02:21,469 --> 00:02:26,349
Look how smoothly this car is going.
Darn, this is fun to drive.

20
00:02:33,606 --> 00:02:35,483
What the... Gang Beom-ryong?

21
00:02:44,617 --> 00:02:46,452
His face looks kind of familiar.

22
00:02:56,837 --> 00:02:58,422
Hey, what's going on?

23
00:02:59,674 --> 00:03:02,969
Hey, Kkot-nim, are you okay? Hey.

24
00:03:03,678 --> 00:03:07,013
Hey, what happened?

25
00:03:07,014 --> 00:03:09,267
- We were attacked, Boss.
- Attacked? Who attacked you?

26
00:03:10,476 --> 00:03:12,394
- Gang Beom-ryong?
- No.

27
00:03:12,395 --> 00:03:14,145
- It was some other guy.
- Another guy?

28
00:03:14,146 --> 00:03:16,356
He showed up out of nowhere
and grabbed Kim Seon-jung's wife

29
00:03:16,357 --> 00:03:17,607
and the woman we saw at the house.

30
00:03:17,608 --> 00:03:18,984
- Yes, that woman.
- He took them and disappeared.

31
00:03:18,985 --> 00:03:20,068
He took them and...

32
00:03:20,069 --> 00:03:22,487
Darn it! Seriously. Gosh, my leg.

33
00:03:22,488 --> 00:03:23,780
Hey, you idiots! What are you doing?

34
00:03:23,781 --> 00:03:26,283
- Get out here, now!
- Boss, what about Kkot-nim?

35
00:03:26,284 --> 00:03:27,577
Just leave that idiot.
Get out here, quick.

36
00:03:28,077 --> 00:03:29,370
Darn it.

37
00:04:02,445 --> 00:04:04,071
They say it's a mild concussion.

38
00:04:05,406 --> 00:04:08,743
I think she'll have to be admitted
to the hospital for observation.

39
00:04:12,580 --> 00:04:13,831
How do you two know each other?

40
00:04:14,165 --> 00:04:16,625
She's the wife
of one of my high school teachers.

41
00:04:16,625 --> 00:04:17,627
A teacher?

42
00:04:20,129 --> 00:04:22,423
What kind of teacher
has gangsters looking for him?

43
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:29,220
What are you trying to imply?
It's not what you think.

44
00:04:29,221 --> 00:04:32,183
Stay away from him for a while.
Don't get mixed up in this.

45
00:04:33,976 --> 00:04:37,104
- What do you know to be saying this?
- Because I'm worried.

46
00:04:38,022 --> 00:04:40,565
My wife almost got dragged away by thugs.

47
00:04:40,566 --> 00:04:41,858
As her husband,
I'm not allowed to say that?

48
00:04:41,859 --> 00:04:43,944
No, you're not.

49
00:04:45,821 --> 00:04:48,699
About how you showed up there earlier

50
00:04:49,825 --> 00:04:51,494
or what that whole fight was about...

51
00:04:51,952 --> 00:04:53,745
Have you ever once given me
a proper explanation?

52
00:04:53,746 --> 00:04:54,747
No, that's...

53
00:04:55,331 --> 00:04:58,042
- What's that got to do with this?
- How could it not?

54
00:05:03,422 --> 00:05:04,674
You...

55
00:05:06,092 --> 00:05:07,927
You've been acting so suspiciously lately

56
00:05:08,761 --> 00:05:11,639
and you haven't even given me
a proper explanation for what's going on.

57
00:05:12,348 --> 00:05:15,225
What wife in the world
would listen to a husband like that?

58
00:05:15,226 --> 00:05:16,435
What reason do I have to trust you?

59
00:05:27,655 --> 00:05:28,698
Honey.

60
00:05:30,032 --> 00:05:31,367
Are you, by any chance...

61
00:05:32,535 --> 00:05:35,621
keeping a secret
that I'm not supposed to know?

62
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,334
Is that it?

63
00:05:51,637 --> 00:05:52,638
O-ran!

64
00:05:53,764 --> 00:05:55,641
Oh, Mr. Kim!

65
00:05:57,017 --> 00:05:58,477
How is my wife?

66
00:05:59,645 --> 00:06:02,148
She's all right. This way, please.

67
00:06:37,558 --> 00:06:38,893
Get lost, you idiots.

68
00:06:39,226 --> 00:06:41,479
Get out. What are you looking at?
Get back to work. Now.

69
00:06:44,273 --> 00:06:47,151
So you're saying
you failed to tie up the loose ends?

70
00:06:47,943 --> 00:06:50,820
I'm sorry. It's just that
some guy showed up out of nowhere--

71
00:06:50,821 --> 00:06:52,740
And this guy who showed up out of nowhere

72
00:06:53,115 --> 00:06:56,075
was with Gang Beom-ryong,
Hwasan Sect's number two?

73
00:06:56,076 --> 00:06:57,077
So why?

74
00:06:58,078 --> 00:06:59,872
You had no idea who this guy was?

75
00:07:00,289 --> 00:07:04,752
Well, that's the thing.
He definitely looked familiar, but...

76
00:07:05,085 --> 00:07:07,797
- I just can't place him--
- If you say you can't remember

77
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:10,423
then what am I supposed to do?

78
00:07:10,424 --> 00:07:12,634
It wasn't that so-called
Martial Arts Master, was it?

79
00:07:12,635 --> 00:07:14,011
No, it was someone else.

80
00:07:19,850 --> 00:07:21,976
Mr. Nam, the owner
of the van that appeared

81
00:07:21,977 --> 00:07:23,646
in front of Kim Seon-jung's house
and at the port.

82
00:07:23,813 --> 00:07:24,896
Have you identified him?

83
00:07:24,897 --> 00:07:26,523
We ran a check, but it was a ghost car.

84
00:07:26,524 --> 00:07:27,775
A ghost car?

85
00:07:32,071 --> 00:07:33,364
My goodness.

86
00:07:34,114 --> 00:07:36,742
Now things are starting to become clear.

87
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:39,829
- What?
- The masked guys Yoo was chasing.

88
00:07:41,038 --> 00:07:43,790
This mysterious man and Gang Beom-ryong.

89
00:07:43,791 --> 00:07:45,125
It fits perfectly, doesn't it?

90
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:47,461
Oh, right.

91
00:07:48,128 --> 00:07:50,588
Now that you mention it... I see.

92
00:07:50,589 --> 00:07:52,674
Gang Beom-ryong,
number two of the Hwasan Sect

93
00:07:52,675 --> 00:07:54,552
the martial arts master,
and the mystery man.

94
00:07:54,969 --> 00:07:57,428
For skilled fighters like them
to just pop up

95
00:07:57,429 --> 00:08:00,182
and interfere with our business
at every turn.

96
00:08:00,975 --> 00:08:02,476
This can't be a coincidence.

97
00:08:02,852 --> 00:08:06,771
I have a feeling
they're specifically targeting one of us

98
00:08:06,772 --> 00:08:08,565
and this is all part of a plan,
don't you think?

99
00:08:08,566 --> 00:08:11,068
Darn it, but why the hell would they?

100
00:08:12,862 --> 00:08:16,031
If we just find one more puzzle piece,
we'll have our answer.

101
00:08:18,033 --> 00:08:21,745
- Chairman Do, should I handle this?
- Handle it?

102
00:08:23,414 --> 00:08:24,497
How?

103
00:08:24,498 --> 00:08:26,583
If we grab Gang Beom-ryong
and beat it out of him

104
00:08:26,584 --> 00:08:27,751
we'll get our answer, won't we?

105
00:08:28,586 --> 00:08:30,087
- Beat it out of him?
- Yes.

106
00:08:30,379 --> 00:08:31,964
- Gang Beom-ryong.
- Yes.

107
00:08:34,174 --> 00:08:36,260
Well, I don't know about that.

108
00:08:37,260 --> 00:08:40,763
Mr. Geum, back when you were
just shining shoes for the Hwasan Sect

109
00:08:40,764 --> 00:08:43,851
wasn't Gang Beom-ryong already
their second-in-command?

110
00:08:45,477 --> 00:08:47,312
Even if you do catch a guy like that
and try to beat him

111
00:08:47,313 --> 00:08:49,731
do you really think he'd talk to you

112
00:08:49,732 --> 00:08:53,736
who's so far beneath him?
I mean, a man has his pride.

113
00:08:54,153 --> 00:08:56,322
- Am I wrong?
- Well...

114
00:08:57,156 --> 00:08:59,991
Chairman Do, actually,
I wasn't that low on the totem pole.

115
00:08:59,992 --> 00:09:02,119
- In the Hwasan Sect, I was--
- For now

116
00:09:02,703 --> 00:09:04,914
Mr. Geum, just focus
on managing Heaven Capital.

117
00:09:05,164 --> 00:09:06,790
- But, Chairman--
- Do you understand?

118
00:09:07,416 --> 00:09:08,417
Chairman...

119
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,170
I asked if you got it.

120
00:09:12,755 --> 00:09:13,756
Yes, I understand.

121
00:09:15,841 --> 00:09:17,134
Let's go.

122
00:09:26,977 --> 00:09:28,270
Darn it.

123
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,486
As if he could beat it out of him.

124
00:09:35,986 --> 00:09:38,489
Mr. Nam, do you have anyone competent?

125
00:09:38,697 --> 00:09:42,076
I need someone who can handle
this job cleanly, with no fuss.

126
00:09:42,368 --> 00:09:45,287
- There are some very skilled hitmen.
- Hitmen?

127
00:09:46,497 --> 00:09:49,375
Okay. Hitmen. I like it.

128
00:09:50,042 --> 00:09:52,086
Set them up right away.

129
00:09:52,753 --> 00:09:54,964
And Mr. Nam,
you should get warmed up, too.

130
00:09:55,756 --> 00:09:58,759
Man, you must have been feeling
cooped up, stuck behind a desk.

131
00:09:59,093 --> 00:10:01,428
It's about time
you got out in the field again.

132
00:10:02,179 --> 00:10:03,764
Yes, sir.

133
00:10:27,079 --> 00:10:28,872
What's with all this drama?

134
00:10:33,210 --> 00:10:34,753
Are you sure about this?

135
00:10:35,295 --> 00:10:36,797
I'm going to come clean.

136
00:10:38,465 --> 00:10:39,800
I have to.

137
00:10:41,260 --> 00:10:42,261
O-ran.

138
00:10:43,220 --> 00:10:44,471
Her family.

139
00:10:46,015 --> 00:10:47,725
And the people of Yeongseon Island.

140
00:10:48,392 --> 00:10:49,893
Before they're in even more danger.

141
00:10:50,686 --> 00:10:51,854
From now on

142
00:10:52,604 --> 00:10:53,981
I have to be more aggressive.

143
00:10:55,482 --> 00:10:56,734
All right.

144
00:10:57,860 --> 00:11:00,571
Then I guess I'll take this chance
to properly introduce myself to your wife.

145
00:11:02,448 --> 00:11:04,867
So after you tell her everything

146
00:11:06,285 --> 00:11:07,619
what happens next?

147
00:11:09,621 --> 00:11:12,374
First, I'm going to meet
with Candidate Kim Seon-jung

148
00:11:13,542 --> 00:11:15,127
and hear what he has to say.

149
00:11:31,643 --> 00:11:33,103
MY LITTLE BROTHER

150
00:11:33,437 --> 00:11:34,855
Jeez, you scared me.

151
00:11:37,191 --> 00:11:39,318
Hey, why aren't you answering my calls?

152
00:11:39,443 --> 00:11:40,444
I was busy.

153
00:11:40,736 --> 00:11:43,989
For a guy who never answers his phone
to be looking for me

154
00:11:44,490 --> 00:11:45,782
means you got your butt kicked again.

155
00:11:45,783 --> 00:11:47,075
No, it's not like that.

156
00:11:47,076 --> 00:11:48,826
What do you mean it's not like that?

157
00:11:48,827 --> 00:11:50,537
I can tell just from your voice.

158
00:11:51,538 --> 00:11:52,539
So who was it this time?

159
00:11:53,749 --> 00:11:58,294
- This fake Yankee jerk.
- Yankee? A foreigner?

160
00:11:58,295 --> 00:12:02,465
I'll explain the details when we meet,
so can you come to where I am now?

161
00:12:02,466 --> 00:12:03,549
All right.

162
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:05,552
- I'll go once I wrap things up here.
- Hey!

163
00:12:06,386 --> 00:12:09,765
The kimchi stew is ready.
Why aren't you coming? Jeez.

164
00:12:09,890 --> 00:12:11,391
I was on the phone with In-gu.

165
00:12:15,687 --> 00:12:17,648
For crying out loud. Geez.

166
00:12:18,649 --> 00:12:21,777
In-gu? He got beat up again?

167
00:12:22,027 --> 00:12:25,530
- That's just In-gu for you.
- What an idiot.

168
00:12:25,531 --> 00:12:28,033
So where is he now?

169
00:12:44,716 --> 00:12:48,720
Yes, Mi-kyung, it's me.
I'm at the hospital right now.

170
00:12:49,513 --> 00:12:52,891
No, not me. Je-sun got a little hurt.

171
00:12:54,101 --> 00:12:55,935
Yes. I'm sorry to ask

172
00:12:55,936 --> 00:12:58,522
but could you tell Nam-il
to come to the hospital?

173
00:13:28,468 --> 00:13:29,678
Hey.

174
00:13:30,679 --> 00:13:31,930
Who's there?

175
00:13:44,651 --> 00:13:45,819
I'm sorry.

176
00:13:52,242 --> 00:13:54,328
- Who are you?
- I couldn't ring the doorbell

177
00:13:54,703 --> 00:13:56,288
because there were too many prying eyes.

178
00:13:57,956 --> 00:13:59,081
O-ran!

179
00:13:59,082 --> 00:14:00,083
Oh, Mr. Kim!

180
00:14:20,395 --> 00:14:23,023
So the reason you dropped out of the race

181
00:14:23,982 --> 00:14:26,359
was because of Han Gyeong-wook's scheme.

182
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:28,195
I was too naive.

183
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:34,200
I never imagined
that he'd attack me like this.

184
00:14:34,201 --> 00:14:36,912
You don't need to blame yourself.
About Han Gyeong-wook...

185
00:14:37,579 --> 00:14:39,080
Ever since his days
at the National Intelligence Service

186
00:14:39,081 --> 00:14:42,750
he has specialized in plots,
threats, and things like that.

187
00:14:42,751 --> 00:14:44,711
Since I couldn't stop
Candidate Han Gyeong-wook

188
00:14:45,420 --> 00:14:49,132
I'm worried there will be more victims

189
00:14:50,509 --> 00:14:53,095
like with the orphanage
and the Heaven Capital debtors.

190
00:14:57,516 --> 00:14:59,977
- We have to stop him somehow.
- Alone?

191
00:15:00,852 --> 00:15:04,481
Do you think that's possible?
Those scumbags...

192
00:15:05,148 --> 00:15:07,067
They are a force to be reckoned with.

193
00:15:07,359 --> 00:15:09,278
I know exactly what they are like.

194
00:15:10,737 --> 00:15:12,447
I'll deal with them.

195
00:15:12,823 --> 00:15:15,492
You just focus on what you have to do

196
00:15:15,951 --> 00:15:19,913
- for the people of Yeongseon Island.
- Okay.

197
00:15:20,664 --> 00:15:21,873
I understand.

198
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,711
I can't take back my withdrawal.

199
00:15:26,962 --> 00:15:29,464
But if there's anything I can do to help

200
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:33,176
- just let me know.
- Thank you.

201
00:15:35,262 --> 00:15:36,596
Oh, and...

202
00:15:39,016 --> 00:15:40,183
About the place

203
00:15:41,143 --> 00:15:42,894
where my wife is helping the victims.

204
00:15:43,770 --> 00:15:45,605
Is it possible to know where that is?

205
00:15:46,815 --> 00:15:51,236
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

206
00:16:00,412 --> 00:16:02,873
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

207
00:16:03,999 --> 00:16:06,501
WE CAN'T BACK DOWN FROM REDEVELOPMENT
THAT KILLS THE COMMON PEOPLE!

208
00:16:13,759 --> 00:16:16,177
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

209
00:16:16,178 --> 00:16:18,347
HANMAEUM SOCIAL DANCE

210
00:16:21,183 --> 00:16:22,767
- Where's Ji-woo's mom?
- She said

211
00:16:22,768 --> 00:16:25,061
she had a dance club meeting
and left suddenly.

212
00:16:25,062 --> 00:16:26,063
Again?

213
00:16:26,521 --> 00:16:28,815
Has she gone crazy for dancing?
What's with her lately?

214
00:16:29,775 --> 00:16:31,818
HANMAEUM SOCIAL DANCE

215
00:16:46,625 --> 00:16:48,251
Bulgae's nephew?

216
00:16:58,678 --> 00:17:01,013
YEONGSON MEDICAL CENTER

217
00:17:01,014 --> 00:17:02,599
Uncle!

218
00:17:05,310 --> 00:17:06,310
What happened?

219
00:17:06,603 --> 00:17:10,065
How can someone who went on a date
become a hit-and-run victim?

220
00:17:11,066 --> 00:17:13,734
- Is he badly hurt?
- There are no external injuries

221
00:17:14,194 --> 00:17:16,570
so don't worry too much.
He'll wake up soon.

222
00:17:18,615 --> 00:17:19,991
Darn it.

223
00:17:22,577 --> 00:17:25,496
I've explained the schedule
for his checkups.

224
00:17:25,497 --> 00:17:27,665
So, who will be staying with him?

225
00:17:27,665 --> 00:17:29,751
- I'll stay.
- All right.

226
00:17:30,210 --> 00:17:32,462
- You?
- Je-sun got hurt because of me

227
00:17:32,963 --> 00:17:34,255
so I think it's only right that I stay.

228
00:17:34,256 --> 00:17:36,632
No, even so, his nephew should stay.

229
00:17:36,633 --> 00:17:38,926
Please give me a chance to repay him.

230
00:17:38,927 --> 00:17:42,347
When I fell into the sea,
Je-sun was the one who took care of me.

231
00:17:44,766 --> 00:17:47,269
Can I ask you something?

232
00:17:48,478 --> 00:17:50,689
What do you think of my uncle?

233
00:17:52,274 --> 00:17:53,941
- What do you mean?
- What?

234
00:17:53,942 --> 00:17:56,528
- Excuse me?
- No, I mean...

235
00:17:57,737 --> 00:17:59,573
Do you find my uncle...

236
00:18:05,036 --> 00:18:06,037
Never mind.

237
00:18:07,205 --> 00:18:08,582
Don't worry about it. Okay.

238
00:18:08,707 --> 00:18:11,417
I should... I should get going.

239
00:18:11,418 --> 00:18:12,961
- Okay.
- Bye.

240
00:18:15,755 --> 00:18:16,882
Hey.

241
00:18:19,176 --> 00:18:21,094
- Have a good time.
- What?

242
00:18:21,553 --> 00:18:22,679
With my uncle.

243
00:18:43,158 --> 00:18:44,409
Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae?

244
00:18:44,993 --> 00:18:46,036
Who might you be?

245
00:18:48,079 --> 00:18:49,623
So we finally meet.

246
00:18:55,128 --> 00:18:58,422
So Yoo In-gu has already been cut loose?

247
00:18:58,423 --> 00:19:01,091
Yes. What's more, a man named Chairman Do

248
00:19:01,092 --> 00:19:02,927
took over everything Yoo In-gu was doing.

249
00:19:02,928 --> 00:19:06,056
So Han Gyeong-wook
won't be affected at all.

250
00:19:07,140 --> 00:19:09,600
Instead, why not focus
on what you mentioned earlier?

251
00:19:09,601 --> 00:19:11,770
The package containing
Han Gyeong-wook's weakness

252
00:19:12,187 --> 00:19:14,940
- and try looking for that?
- The package?

253
00:19:15,065 --> 00:19:17,025
I mean, you said you have
the radio receiver.

254
00:19:17,317 --> 00:19:18,902
So is there really no way to find it?

255
00:19:20,237 --> 00:19:23,948
The receiver is supposed to go off
when I get within 10m of the package

256
00:19:23,949 --> 00:19:27,576
but I've searched all over
Yeongseon Island for the past ten years

257
00:19:27,577 --> 00:19:29,162
and the receiver has never gone off.

258
00:19:30,038 --> 00:19:33,124
I even went to Bulgae's house,
but there was no signal there either.

259
00:19:34,334 --> 00:19:36,085
It seems Bulgae

260
00:19:36,086 --> 00:19:40,006
likely hid it in a secret place
only he knows.

261
00:19:42,259 --> 00:19:44,511
Je-sun probably doesn't know
about the package.

262
00:19:46,263 --> 00:19:47,471
Right now

263
00:19:47,472 --> 00:19:50,767
you seem to think
Bong Je-sun is faking his amnesia.

264
00:19:50,976 --> 00:19:52,102
But no.

265
00:19:52,602 --> 00:19:56,022
The Je-sun I saw wasn't faking it.

266
00:20:02,946 --> 00:20:06,992
Since we have no leads on that package,
we need to find another way, and fast.

267
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:10,536
I heard Han Gyeong-wook is deeply involved
in the recent redevelopment project

268
00:20:10,537 --> 00:20:12,121
on Yeongseon Island.

269
00:20:12,122 --> 00:20:14,498
- Yes.
- Seeing how he's pushing to become mayor

270
00:20:14,499 --> 00:20:16,208
and even mobilizing Heaven Capital

271
00:20:16,209 --> 00:20:18,378
this can't be just an ordinary project.

272
00:20:19,045 --> 00:20:22,257
Please look into what's going on
behind the scenes of that project.

273
00:20:22,924 --> 00:20:24,550
Here on Yeongseon Island

274
00:20:24,551 --> 00:20:27,052
we'll dig into the activities of that guy

275
00:20:27,053 --> 00:20:28,346
Chairman Do and Han Gyeong-wook.

276
00:20:29,139 --> 00:20:31,766
All right. I'll investigate
as soon as I get back to the office.

277
00:20:32,225 --> 00:20:35,979
And you have to get the dance club members
to back off from this.

278
00:20:36,438 --> 00:20:39,733
- They could be in danger.
- Well...

279
00:20:40,191 --> 00:20:43,736
They're Yeongseon Island natives
who are directly tied to this issue

280
00:20:43,737 --> 00:20:47,365
- so it won't be easy to persuade them.
- I'll try to persuade them myself.

281
00:20:47,657 --> 00:20:50,660
- You will?
- It's about my wife, after all.

282
00:20:52,037 --> 00:20:53,371
That's true.

283
00:20:55,707 --> 00:20:57,876
All right. Let's proceed that way, then.

284
00:20:58,126 --> 00:20:59,210
Okay.

285
00:21:36,706 --> 00:21:38,375
What is it, so late?

286
00:21:43,630 --> 00:21:46,299
About your wife...
Did things get resolved?

287
00:21:47,384 --> 00:21:50,679
Before I go and take care of it,
there's something I need to tell you.

288
00:21:52,847 --> 00:21:55,016
Why Officer Park Mi-kyung was there

289
00:21:55,308 --> 00:21:57,185
and what her relationship is with Bulgae.

290
00:21:58,144 --> 00:21:59,437
I've figured it all out.

291
00:22:04,401 --> 00:22:07,444
But Mi-kyung is just a patrol officer.
What can she do?

292
00:22:07,445 --> 00:22:09,364
I mean, does she even know
who she's up against?

293
00:22:09,739 --> 00:22:12,325
She doesn't know what it's like
because she hasn't been through it.

294
00:22:18,665 --> 00:22:20,875
Hey. If you were me

295
00:22:22,293 --> 00:22:23,545
what would you do?

296
00:22:24,129 --> 00:22:27,716
- You tell her to quit right now.
- Hey, it's easier said than done.

297
00:22:28,091 --> 00:22:29,758
If I bring up my past

298
00:22:29,759 --> 00:22:31,760
and tell Mi-kyung to quit what she's doing

299
00:22:31,761 --> 00:22:33,555
you think I don't know how she'd react?

300
00:22:33,972 --> 00:22:35,639
Would the words come easily
if you were me?

301
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:37,475
So you know she's walking into danger

302
00:22:37,892 --> 00:22:39,436
and you're just going to stand by
and watch?

303
00:22:43,398 --> 00:22:45,400
Because you're scared
of what she'll think of you

304
00:22:45,859 --> 00:22:48,945
- you'll just sit back and do nothing?
- Who said I would do nothing?

305
00:22:49,362 --> 00:22:51,531
Think about what's really important.

306
00:22:52,449 --> 00:22:56,327
Your pride or her safety.

307
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:24,939
- Where's Ji-woo?
- At the restaurant.

308
00:23:25,940 --> 00:23:27,609
I left him with my dad for a little while.

309
00:23:27,984 --> 00:23:30,612
I couldn't let Ji-woo see us fight.

310
00:23:42,999 --> 00:23:44,751
I thought you'd be here yesterday

311
00:23:46,127 --> 00:23:47,378
but you're just showing up now?

312
00:23:48,671 --> 00:23:50,298
That's just like you.

313
00:23:51,716 --> 00:23:52,966
I needed to clear my head.

314
00:23:52,967 --> 00:23:55,011
Not because you were busy
thinking up an excuse?

315
00:24:00,433 --> 00:24:03,603
I was so buried in my own work

316
00:24:04,437 --> 00:24:06,689
that I didn't even realize
what you were going through

317
00:24:07,023 --> 00:24:08,650
or what you were getting into.

318
00:24:09,692 --> 00:24:11,486
I wasn't paying attention
like I should have.

319
00:24:14,739 --> 00:24:16,366
The K-Pop dance club.

320
00:24:17,617 --> 00:24:19,702
You don't go there just to dance, do you?

321
00:24:21,037 --> 00:24:23,122
- What?
- I met with Kim Seon-jung.

322
00:24:23,998 --> 00:24:27,210
He asked me to make you quit
what you're doing.

323
00:24:29,003 --> 00:24:30,630
You were looking into me.

324
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:34,092
Helping the victims of Heaven Capital.

325
00:24:34,676 --> 00:24:37,178
I get what you're trying to do,
but you need to stop.

326
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:39,304
They aren't just gangsters.

327
00:24:39,305 --> 00:24:42,683
What do you know that gives you the right
to tell me to stop?

328
00:24:42,684 --> 00:24:43,685
I know them very well.

329
00:24:45,979 --> 00:24:48,147
They're the ones who made me this way.

330
00:24:49,190 --> 00:24:50,316
What?

331
00:24:55,738 --> 00:24:59,909
Do you remember what I told you?
About why I came to Yeongseon Island.

332
00:25:02,370 --> 00:25:04,163
You said that
you were at a trading company

333
00:25:04,581 --> 00:25:07,250
and you were framed for embezzlement
and kicked out.

334
00:25:07,667 --> 00:25:10,587
- You came here to clear your head.
- That was a lie.

335
00:25:18,803 --> 00:25:20,638
The place I worked...

336
00:25:29,355 --> 00:25:30,815
It was the National Intelligence Service.

337
00:25:31,858 --> 00:25:34,819
I was a black ops agent for the NIS.

338
00:25:37,906 --> 00:25:39,324
A black ops agent?

339
00:25:40,366 --> 00:25:44,162
You mean like in the movies,
shooting guns and breaking in?

340
00:25:44,537 --> 00:25:47,165
- Is that what you're talking about?
- Yes, something like that.

341
00:25:47,290 --> 00:25:48,541
Well, do you by any chance...

342
00:25:50,084 --> 00:25:51,335
Do you have a criminal record?

343
00:25:51,336 --> 00:25:53,045
Is that why you're telling
this ridiculous lie...

344
00:25:53,046 --> 00:25:54,297
I know it's hard to believe.

345
00:25:55,882 --> 00:25:58,967
I was framed during an operation
and had to go on the run.

346
00:25:58,968 --> 00:26:00,636
I came to Yeongseon Island

347
00:26:00,637 --> 00:26:02,597
to find a clue that would clear my name.

348
00:26:03,723 --> 00:26:06,350
Well, I didn't think ten years would go by

349
00:26:06,351 --> 00:26:09,061
but the person who framed me
and forced me on the run

350
00:26:09,062 --> 00:26:13,024
is now using Heaven Capital
to plot something on Yeongseon Island.

351
00:26:13,274 --> 00:26:14,984
He's extremely dangerous.

352
00:26:17,403 --> 00:26:18,696
So, just for a little while

353
00:26:19,322 --> 00:26:20,657
close the restaurant

354
00:26:21,783 --> 00:26:24,035
- and leave Yeongseon Island.
- So then...

355
00:26:25,495 --> 00:26:31,459
From the very beginning,
you've been lying to me for ten years.

356
00:26:35,546 --> 00:26:36,798
I'm sorry.

357
00:26:39,467 --> 00:26:40,842
Once I cleared my name

358
00:26:40,843 --> 00:26:42,345
and was reinstated at the NIS

359
00:26:43,346 --> 00:26:44,596
I planned to tell you in a grand way.

360
00:26:44,597 --> 00:26:46,640
So I could proudly face you
and our Ji-woo.

361
00:26:46,641 --> 00:26:47,725
Clear your name?

362
00:26:49,394 --> 00:26:50,727
Is that why

363
00:26:50,728 --> 00:26:52,730
you were always out
running around like that?

364
00:26:53,147 --> 00:26:54,440
I mean, how...

365
00:26:54,565 --> 00:26:58,820
How could you do something like that
without even consulting me?

366
00:26:58,987 --> 00:27:02,490
And who are you to tell me
to leave Yeongseon Island?

367
00:27:03,533 --> 00:27:05,033
I mean, right now

368
00:27:05,034 --> 00:27:07,036
where would I even go?
I have nowhere to go.

369
00:27:11,374 --> 00:27:14,210
Oh, the dance club. Go stay there for now.

370
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:17,296
There are no security cameras there,
and it seems safe.

371
00:27:17,630 --> 00:27:20,341
Since they know your face,
they'll use security cameras to track

372
00:27:20,466 --> 00:27:23,593
you, your father, and our Ji-woo.

373
00:27:23,594 --> 00:27:25,680
There's no telling what they'll do.

374
00:27:26,848 --> 00:27:28,141
Our Ji-woo?

375
00:27:35,940 --> 00:27:37,650
The fact that up until now

376
00:27:39,986 --> 00:27:41,863
I couldn't be honest with you...

377
00:27:43,364 --> 00:27:44,573
I'm truly sorry.

378
00:27:44,574 --> 00:27:47,702
I know that you're angry
and it's hard to accept the situation.

379
00:27:48,369 --> 00:27:50,871
I'd feel the same way
if I were in your shoes.

380
00:27:50,872 --> 00:27:53,291
But, just this once

381
00:27:53,666 --> 00:27:54,709
for our family

382
00:27:55,084 --> 00:27:58,337
and for our Ji-woo's sake,
please do as I say.

383
00:28:00,131 --> 00:28:02,842
Please trust me
and just for a little while

384
00:28:05,178 --> 00:28:06,429
go somewhere safe.

385
00:28:08,848 --> 00:28:10,475
I'm begging you, O-ran.

386
00:28:17,690 --> 00:28:18,941
Leave.

387
00:28:21,235 --> 00:28:23,237
You're a husband
who lied to me for ten years.

388
00:28:23,696 --> 00:28:25,782
I don't know how
I'm supposed to trust you.

389
00:28:29,452 --> 00:28:31,079
Give me some time to think.

390
00:28:35,917 --> 00:28:37,168
All right.

391
00:28:38,294 --> 00:28:39,921
Let me know when you're ready.

392
00:29:08,449 --> 00:29:09,492
Hey, you.

393
00:29:14,330 --> 00:29:16,124
- Never mind.
- Geez, come on.

394
00:29:16,874 --> 00:29:19,043
You can't even ask him one thing?

395
00:29:20,628 --> 00:29:21,629
Ho-myeong.

396
00:29:22,004 --> 00:29:26,843
Are you really
an NIS agent or whatever it's called?

397
00:29:27,260 --> 00:29:31,222
It's just that we overheard
you and O-ran fighting.

398
00:29:39,564 --> 00:29:41,774
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you all sooner.

399
00:29:41,983 --> 00:29:44,360
So it's true. It is.

400
00:29:49,448 --> 00:29:50,867
- Mi-kyung.
- My goodness.

401
00:29:53,411 --> 00:29:54,704
You startled me.

402
00:29:55,705 --> 00:29:57,540
What are you doing here?

403
00:29:58,416 --> 00:29:59,458
Could you spare

404
00:30:00,543 --> 00:30:03,379
a moment to talk with me?

405
00:30:21,564 --> 00:30:23,149
It's so late

406
00:30:24,066 --> 00:30:26,152
that my convenience store
is the only place still open.

407
00:30:26,277 --> 00:30:27,320
It's fine.

408
00:30:28,237 --> 00:30:30,281
We don't need to talk for long anyway.

409
00:30:30,907 --> 00:30:32,658
You don't have much time, do you?

410
00:30:33,951 --> 00:30:36,704
- Excuse me?
- That's what your employee told me.

411
00:30:37,079 --> 00:30:38,915
That you're someone with big plans

412
00:30:39,373 --> 00:30:41,791
so you don't have time
for someone like me.

413
00:30:41,792 --> 00:30:43,419
That's absolutely not true.

414
00:30:44,045 --> 00:30:47,048
- I apologize on his behalf.
- It's fine.

415
00:30:48,507 --> 00:30:50,635
It went in one ear and out the other.

416
00:30:52,970 --> 00:30:55,264
So, what did you want to say?

417
00:30:56,307 --> 00:30:57,350
The reason

418
00:30:58,309 --> 00:31:00,228
I couldn't make it to our meeting that day

419
00:31:01,187 --> 00:31:03,064
was because I didn't want to tell you

420
00:31:04,106 --> 00:31:05,650
about my past.

421
00:31:06,567 --> 00:31:07,610
Your past?

422
00:31:08,694 --> 00:31:10,404
Yes, I...

423
00:31:11,113 --> 00:31:13,115
Before I became the owner
of this convenience store

424
00:31:17,203 --> 00:31:19,038
I was in a gang.

425
00:31:22,416 --> 00:31:23,751
A gang?

426
00:31:26,212 --> 00:31:27,213
Wait.

427
00:31:28,506 --> 00:31:31,509
You're not talking about
being a gangster, are you?

428
00:31:32,051 --> 00:31:33,511
That's right. A gangster.

429
00:31:33,928 --> 00:31:35,846
The kind that uses his fists
and beats people up.

430
00:31:37,181 --> 00:31:38,599
That's the kind of gangster I was.

431
00:31:42,311 --> 00:31:44,312
Is that why you came looking for me?
To tell me this?

432
00:31:44,313 --> 00:31:45,314
Mi-kyung.

433
00:31:47,608 --> 00:31:50,569
It's because I found out
what you've been up to recently.

434
00:31:51,320 --> 00:31:52,946
What you're doing right now

435
00:31:52,947 --> 00:31:54,573
and the stuff related to Heaven Capital.

436
00:31:56,784 --> 00:31:58,077
You need to stop.

437
00:32:02,832 --> 00:32:04,416
Those guys at Heaven Capital.

438
00:32:04,417 --> 00:32:07,503
They're not the kind of people
a patrol officer like you can handle.

439
00:32:07,878 --> 00:32:10,922
If they think you're in their way,
they'll get rid of you

440
00:32:10,923 --> 00:32:12,007
without a second thought.

441
00:32:12,008 --> 00:32:14,969
So all this stuff you're doing,
just stop all of it.

442
00:32:16,053 --> 00:32:17,638
If you get caught,
you'll be in big trouble.

443
00:32:20,975 --> 00:32:23,102
What right do you have

444
00:32:23,269 --> 00:32:25,938
to suddenly show up
and tell me what to do?

445
00:32:26,105 --> 00:32:28,523
I mean, it's not like
we've even been on a date.

446
00:32:28,524 --> 00:32:30,901
You have no right to tell me what to do.

447
00:32:34,363 --> 00:32:35,614
And...

448
00:32:36,741 --> 00:32:39,243
in case you forgot, I'm a police officer.

449
00:32:40,953 --> 00:32:43,831
The kind that arrests gangsters
and throws them in jail.

450
00:32:45,499 --> 00:32:47,043
And yet you're telling me

451
00:32:47,543 --> 00:32:50,087
to quit because you know better
as an ex-gangster?

452
00:32:53,299 --> 00:32:55,343
- How could you say that?
- I know.

453
00:32:55,843 --> 00:32:58,386
I knew how you'd see me
if I told you this.

454
00:32:58,387 --> 00:33:00,680
But I couldn't stand by
when it's so obvious

455
00:33:00,681 --> 00:33:02,016
you're walking into danger.

456
00:33:03,142 --> 00:33:04,810
- I couldn't pretend not to know.
- Why?

457
00:33:06,312 --> 00:33:07,938
You should have just pretended
you didn't know.

458
00:33:08,856 --> 00:33:10,107
Then we could have just stayed

459
00:33:11,359 --> 00:33:13,944
as the store owner and a customer.

460
00:33:14,862 --> 00:33:17,323
That's all we could have been,
couldn't we?

461
00:33:17,740 --> 00:33:22,411
I don't care how you see me.

462
00:33:23,412 --> 00:33:25,873
In any case, for your own safety

463
00:33:26,916 --> 00:33:29,251
I hope you'll give my words
one more serious thought.

464
00:33:34,590 --> 00:33:36,384
I should get going.

465
00:34:36,068 --> 00:34:39,487
MY DAD

466
00:34:43,367 --> 00:34:44,993
For our family

467
00:34:44,994 --> 00:34:48,164
and for our Ji-woo's sake,
please do as I say.

468
00:34:48,998 --> 00:34:51,458
Please trust me
and just for a little while

469
00:34:52,083 --> 00:34:53,460
go somewhere safe.

470
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:55,629
I'm begging you, O-ran.

471
00:36:20,464 --> 00:36:22,424
Yeongseon Steel.

472
00:36:39,608 --> 00:36:41,443
My savior.

473
00:36:49,702 --> 00:36:50,953
Family.

474
00:37:05,426 --> 00:37:08,178
Je-sun, in the field...

475
00:37:08,512 --> 00:37:11,056
The doll.

476
00:37:14,101 --> 00:37:15,436
The doll.

477
00:37:52,890 --> 00:37:54,141
Darn it.

478
00:37:59,229 --> 00:38:03,233
The receiver is supposed to go off
when I get within 10m of the package.

479
00:38:20,334 --> 00:38:22,836
You're here? Boss, hold on.

480
00:38:23,045 --> 00:38:25,255
What's with your eyes?
Are you sick or something?

481
00:38:25,714 --> 00:38:28,842
- They're really red.
- Let's hurry. We'll be late.

482
00:38:43,941 --> 00:38:46,484
Seriously, what kind
of K-pop dance team is this?

483
00:38:46,485 --> 00:38:48,946
They've got Prosecutor Gang,
Bulgae, and the cop.

484
00:38:49,697 --> 00:38:51,532
And on top of that, even Mr. Jeong's wife.

485
00:38:52,616 --> 00:38:55,661
Hey, Ho-myeong. How did your wife take it?

486
00:38:58,163 --> 00:39:00,124
Of course she's very disappointed.

487
00:39:00,582 --> 00:39:05,462
So, as soon as I crush Yoo In-gu,
Chairman Do, and Han Gyeong-wook

488
00:39:05,796 --> 00:39:07,047
and we talk again...

489
00:39:10,426 --> 00:39:11,927
I hope she'll understand then.

490
00:39:12,678 --> 00:39:13,679
Right.

491
00:39:14,263 --> 00:39:16,557
We just have to finish
before it's too late. Then...

492
00:39:17,141 --> 00:39:20,519
That angry look in her eyes
will probably die down a bit.

493
00:39:32,698 --> 00:39:36,326
So, based on your talk
with Prosecutor Gang yesterday

494
00:39:36,785 --> 00:39:39,163
what we need to do at this point

495
00:39:39,621 --> 00:39:42,749
is to dig into what this
redevelopment project is all about, right?

496
00:39:42,750 --> 00:39:44,042
There's definitely
something shady about it.

497
00:39:44,376 --> 00:39:46,837
Han Gyeong-wook must have bribed
someone at the Imcheon city hall.

498
00:39:47,087 --> 00:39:50,466
You should head over there
and find out everything about the project.

499
00:39:50,924 --> 00:39:53,551
We'll go meet Prosecutor Gang
and wrap things up.

500
00:39:53,552 --> 00:39:55,387
Okay. I'll hurry.

501
00:39:59,141 --> 00:40:00,893
- Let's go.
- Yes, let's go.

502
00:40:01,685 --> 00:40:03,645
- Hey, Gong-bok.
- Yes?

503
00:40:06,982 --> 00:40:09,443
Well... About Mi-kyung.

504
00:40:12,654 --> 00:40:14,698
- Never mind.
- It's nothing, right?

505
00:40:19,870 --> 00:40:20,995
Darn it.

506
00:40:20,996 --> 00:40:23,498
What is it? What?
What about that police officer?

507
00:40:23,499 --> 00:40:26,000
Well... No matter how much
I think about it

508
00:40:26,001 --> 00:40:29,212
spying on the Heaven Capital guys
is just too dangerous.

509
00:40:29,213 --> 00:40:31,590
So, I want you to go and...

510
00:40:33,258 --> 00:40:34,634
You want me to what?

511
00:40:34,635 --> 00:40:37,137
- You want me to watch over her?
- I mean...

512
00:40:38,096 --> 00:40:42,100
It is related to our work, after all.
And that area is your specialty.

513
00:40:42,226 --> 00:40:43,935
Why should I use my specialty for that?

514
00:40:43,936 --> 00:40:46,688
She's a cop. She can take care of herself.

515
00:40:46,814 --> 00:40:50,024
Come on, how can you be so heartless?

516
00:40:50,025 --> 00:40:53,277
I mean, she's a long-time customer.
Think of it as customer service.

517
00:40:53,278 --> 00:40:55,822
Just go and support her
if she needs anything.

518
00:40:55,823 --> 00:40:57,949
We closed down the convenience store.

519
00:40:57,950 --> 00:40:59,701
What damn customer service
are you talking about?

520
00:41:00,577 --> 00:41:02,871
Fine. Just forget it.

521
00:41:12,130 --> 00:41:14,341
- I just have to watch her, right?
- Yes.

522
00:41:14,842 --> 00:41:16,509
You know me, right? I'm allergic to cops.

523
00:41:16,510 --> 00:41:19,304
- This is the last time.
- I know, Gong-bok. Let's go.

524
00:41:21,348 --> 00:41:22,558
Gosh, seriously.

525
00:41:52,713 --> 00:41:54,256
We've located their base.

526
00:42:39,885 --> 00:42:43,095
Excuse me.
Have you seen Bong Je-sun from room 1301?

527
00:42:43,096 --> 00:42:44,805
- Bong Je-sun?
- Yes.

528
00:42:44,806 --> 00:42:47,059
He was here when I checked
his blood pressure last night.

529
00:42:47,517 --> 00:42:50,103
- He's not in his room?
- Oh, okay. I understand.

530
00:42:59,821 --> 00:43:01,865
Bong Je-sun is gone.

531
00:43:02,532 --> 00:43:06,535
- When? When did he disappear?
- I don't know.

532
00:43:06,536 --> 00:43:08,288
He was gone when I woke up this morning.

533
00:43:08,872 --> 00:43:10,748
His clothes are gone too

534
00:43:10,749 --> 00:43:12,417
and he hasn't been officially discharged.

535
00:43:12,668 --> 00:43:16,004
Where did he go? Are we going to lose him?

536
00:43:16,588 --> 00:43:20,550
I knew this would happen,
so I put a tracker on him yesterday.

537
00:43:21,468 --> 00:43:23,177
Look at you.

538
00:43:23,178 --> 00:43:25,055
There's that old NIS training.

539
00:43:25,263 --> 00:43:27,432
So, where is that guy now?

540
00:43:30,852 --> 00:43:32,688
What? What's wrong with this thing?

541
00:43:33,063 --> 00:43:35,064
What? It says he's still in the hospital.

542
00:43:35,065 --> 00:43:37,317
But I already searched
the entire hospital.

543
00:43:44,533 --> 00:43:45,701
What?

544
00:43:55,919 --> 00:43:57,545
Look at this guy.

545
00:43:57,546 --> 00:43:59,631
So, what happened?
Did we lose him, or what?

546
00:44:00,048 --> 00:44:01,299
I think he figured it out.

547
00:44:02,801 --> 00:44:04,218
Figured what out?

548
00:44:04,219 --> 00:44:07,221
I told you. Bulgae is not an amnesiac.

549
00:44:07,222 --> 00:44:10,474
He was afraid his act would be blown
after seeing me yesterday

550
00:44:10,475 --> 00:44:11,852
so he must have run away.

551
00:44:16,023 --> 00:44:18,275
What? Prosecutor Gang, what are you doing?

552
00:44:19,484 --> 00:44:20,902
Je-sun.

553
00:44:27,951 --> 00:44:30,954
I heard the chicken soup here
is delicious.

554
00:44:38,336 --> 00:44:41,089
- My gosh.
- Just look at this place. Darn it.

555
00:44:42,507 --> 00:44:44,342
It's cozy.

556
00:44:46,136 --> 00:44:47,554
My goodness.

557
00:44:47,763 --> 00:44:49,305
HWANG HWA-SAN SENTENCED TO LIFE
FOR MURDERING KWON SOON-BOK

558
00:44:49,306 --> 00:44:52,726
- These darn stalkers. Darn it.
- What?

559
00:44:54,686 --> 00:44:57,773
Mr. Geum, you are quite photogenic.

560
00:45:06,948 --> 00:45:08,325
THE DEATH OF NATIONAL SECURITY DIRECTOR
KWON SOON-BOK

561
00:45:23,173 --> 00:45:24,174
REPUBLIC OF KOREA PASSPORT

562
00:45:31,640 --> 00:45:33,100
What?

563
00:45:33,683 --> 00:45:35,060
Chairman.

564
00:45:37,395 --> 00:45:42,567
I think we came to the right place.
Man, I really don't get it.

565
00:45:43,777 --> 00:45:48,156
It doesn't seem to be about money.
So why are they pulling this crap?

566
00:45:50,909 --> 00:45:52,452
Take a look at this photo.

567
00:45:54,955 --> 00:45:58,959
SEPTEMBER 2010, FEBRUARY 2010, MAY 2010

568
00:46:13,598 --> 00:46:18,103
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

569
00:46:21,481 --> 00:46:24,568
If you don't pay next time,
I won't be making any more deliveries.

570
00:46:25,735 --> 00:46:27,195
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

571
00:46:27,445 --> 00:46:29,739
- Oh, right!
- Gosh, you scared me.

572
00:46:30,323 --> 00:46:31,783
The Chinese food delivery guy.

573
00:46:32,993 --> 00:46:34,452
Chairman, that guy...

574
00:46:34,786 --> 00:46:37,664
- He was with Gang Beom-ryong
- The day before yesterday?

575
00:46:38,790 --> 00:46:40,542
- The delivery guy?
- Yes.

576
00:46:49,092 --> 00:46:51,011
So this is how it all connects.

577
00:46:53,722 --> 00:46:56,516
You put the camper van back
to how it was, right?

578
00:46:56,766 --> 00:47:00,395
Yes. I even planted a bug, as instructed.

579
00:47:01,521 --> 00:47:03,063
Okay, good job.

580
00:47:03,064 --> 00:47:06,275
We absolutely cannot leave
a single trace that we were there.

581
00:47:06,276 --> 00:47:10,196
And for now, tell the hitmen
to just tail them.

582
00:47:10,197 --> 00:47:12,198
Wouldn't it be better to eliminate them?

583
00:47:12,199 --> 00:47:14,409
No. Absolutely not.

584
00:47:15,577 --> 00:47:18,495
The way I see it, these guys
and Deputy Director Han have a past

585
00:47:18,496 --> 00:47:22,041
and I'm sure there's
some spectacular drama involved.

586
00:47:22,042 --> 00:47:24,251
Didn't you see the news clippings

587
00:47:24,252 --> 00:47:26,463
about the ferry incident
from ten years ago and the Hwasan Sect?

588
00:47:26,713 --> 00:47:29,549
You take one look
and the answer is obvious.

589
00:47:29,758 --> 00:47:33,844
If their target was Han from the start,
that means I'm holding a hand

590
00:47:33,845 --> 00:47:35,846
with far more to gain than lose, right?

591
00:47:35,847 --> 00:47:39,225
I can't just throw away a lucky hand
that fell into my lap.

592
00:47:39,226 --> 00:47:41,019
What are you planning to do?

593
00:47:42,979 --> 00:47:45,439
To be the winner in this game

594
00:47:45,440 --> 00:47:49,319
you need to hold a few jokers
to shake up the board.

595
00:47:50,278 --> 00:47:54,199
For now, maybe I'll poke
at Deputy Director Han first?

596
00:47:56,576 --> 00:47:58,370
Gosh, this will be fun.

597
00:47:59,663 --> 00:48:01,122
I'm curious

598
00:48:02,123 --> 00:48:04,668
how he'll react.

599
00:48:07,504 --> 00:48:12,258
Yes, I confirmed he left the hospital
and hailed a taxi.

600
00:48:12,259 --> 00:48:13,592
YEONGSON MEDICAL CENTER

601
00:48:13,593 --> 00:48:14,970
And...

602
00:48:16,346 --> 00:48:18,890
He returned to the hospital
exactly five hours later.

603
00:48:19,599 --> 00:48:22,811
Got it. Send me the video.

604
00:48:43,081 --> 00:48:44,748
Like I said

605
00:48:44,749 --> 00:48:47,043
I just went out to get something to eat.

606
00:48:47,460 --> 00:48:49,963
At that hour? After pulling out your IV?

607
00:48:50,171 --> 00:48:51,298
Yes.

608
00:48:52,090 --> 00:48:55,217
Prosecutor Gang was having a hard time
because of me

609
00:48:55,218 --> 00:48:56,510
sleeping in a chair at the hospital.

610
00:48:56,511 --> 00:48:58,762
So I wanted to repay her somehow.

611
00:48:58,763 --> 00:49:00,764
Why would you say that's on you, Je-sun?

612
00:49:00,765 --> 00:49:02,517
You were injured trying to save me.

613
00:49:03,268 --> 00:49:05,854
Then what about this tracking device
that was on your hoodie?

614
00:49:06,479 --> 00:49:08,148
Why did you deliberately remove it
before you left?

615
00:49:08,565 --> 00:49:09,566
Tracking...

616
00:49:10,233 --> 00:49:12,068
I had this on me?

617
00:49:13,111 --> 00:49:14,446
Why?

618
00:49:15,113 --> 00:49:16,488
Playing dumb, are you?

619
00:49:16,489 --> 00:49:19,451
No, I'm not playing dumb.
I really didn't know it was there.

620
00:49:21,411 --> 00:49:24,706
Maybe it fell off
when I put the hoodie on?

621
00:49:30,086 --> 00:49:31,338
To be honest...

622
00:49:32,464 --> 00:49:35,758
About what you two and Prosecutor Gang
told me about my past...

623
00:49:35,759 --> 00:49:39,804
I still can't believe it.
I'm just an ordinary office worker.

624
00:49:41,973 --> 00:49:45,393
The idea that I was
such a strong and ruthless agent...

625
00:49:47,937 --> 00:49:51,691
But since you all say so, it must be true.

626
00:49:51,941 --> 00:49:55,069
Even though I don't remember

627
00:49:55,070 --> 00:49:58,489
if I did something wrong
to you two in the past

628
00:49:58,490 --> 00:50:03,078
I want to apologize now.
Yes, I'm truly sorry.

629
00:50:32,190 --> 00:50:35,693
Oh my, Je-sun.
My goodness, what are you doing?

630
00:50:36,778 --> 00:50:38,070
Ho-myeong, what was that for?

631
00:50:38,071 --> 00:50:39,863
He took the hit on purpose.
Can't you see that?

632
00:50:39,864 --> 00:50:41,366
- Oh my, Je-sun.
- Hey.

633
00:50:41,491 --> 00:50:44,535
- Drop the act, you goddamn spy.
- It hurts so much.

634
00:50:44,536 --> 00:50:46,745
Geez, don't you think that's too much?

635
00:50:46,746 --> 00:50:48,540
He's a patient who hasn't fully recovered.

636
00:50:48,665 --> 00:50:51,875
Yes, even I couldn't have dodged that.
Did you have to throw it that hard?

637
00:50:51,876 --> 00:50:54,128
Look, Prosecutor,
you don't seem to get it.

638
00:50:54,129 --> 00:50:57,089
This guy is Bulgae, the most elite agent
of the Ministry of People's Armed Forces.

639
00:50:57,090 --> 00:50:59,007
In the middle of Washington, D.C.,
he evaded the CIA

640
00:50:59,008 --> 00:51:00,759
and helped
all the North Korean hackers escape.

641
00:51:00,760 --> 00:51:03,011
In Sichuan province,
he beat 20 Triad men to a pulp.

642
00:51:03,012 --> 00:51:05,222
He's Bulgae, a human weapon
trained by North Korea.

643
00:51:05,223 --> 00:51:08,851
- He's not a pushover.
- I think you've got it wrong.

644
00:51:08,852 --> 00:51:11,103
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

645
00:51:11,104 --> 00:51:13,480
Look how frail he is.
How's he supposed to take on the CIA?

646
00:51:13,481 --> 00:51:16,443
Get real. You need to make sense.

647
00:51:18,987 --> 00:51:20,321
Yes.

648
00:51:22,198 --> 00:51:23,366
I...

649
00:51:24,492 --> 00:51:27,412
I must have been a really terrible person.

650
00:51:27,871 --> 00:51:31,665
Seeing how you're still this angry
at me after ten years...

651
00:51:31,666 --> 00:51:33,042
I really...

652
00:51:33,877 --> 00:51:36,336
I really don't remember anything.

653
00:51:36,337 --> 00:51:39,632
But I sincerely apologize. I am so sorry.

654
00:51:40,383 --> 00:51:41,967
What's with the sudden apology?

655
00:51:41,968 --> 00:51:43,510
- Exactly.
- Are you okay?

656
00:51:43,511 --> 00:51:46,263
This is not a situation
where you need to apologize.

657
00:51:46,264 --> 00:51:49,766
I'm telling you, it's an act!
Hey, you're a hell of an actor.

658
00:51:49,767 --> 00:51:52,811
Where did you learn to act?
Do they teach that in North Korea now?

659
00:51:52,812 --> 00:51:55,648
- Hey, wait.
- Okay.

660
00:51:56,399 --> 00:52:00,486
I can't atone for my past mistakes,
but perhaps...

661
00:52:00,487 --> 00:52:03,698
Is there a way I can help you two?

662
00:52:04,532 --> 00:52:06,993
- Help us?
- Yes.

663
00:52:07,243 --> 00:52:09,870
- What the hell are you plotting?
- Hey, what's wrong with you?

664
00:52:09,871 --> 00:52:13,165
I'm not plotting anything.
I'm doing this for me. For myself.

665
00:52:13,166 --> 00:52:15,209
That package
I supposedly disappeared with.

666
00:52:15,210 --> 00:52:18,212
If I just have that package,
you said you could stop

667
00:52:18,213 --> 00:52:20,465
what the Heaven Capital guys
are planning, right?

668
00:52:21,007 --> 00:52:23,343
I have a score to settle
with those guys, too.

669
00:52:24,802 --> 00:52:28,305
I just figured if I stick with you two,
the ones who know my past

670
00:52:28,306 --> 00:52:31,059
maybe I'll start to remember something.

671
00:52:31,684 --> 00:52:33,435
Hey, listen to him. It all makes sense.

672
00:52:33,436 --> 00:52:35,395
If he gets his memory back
and we find the package

673
00:52:35,396 --> 00:52:36,773
isn't that the best
we can hope for right now?

674
00:52:40,944 --> 00:52:44,112
I'll go get you another one
of those drinks you were drinking.

675
00:52:44,113 --> 00:52:46,950
- No, it's fine. Are you okay?
- Yes.

676
00:52:48,743 --> 00:52:51,579
Gosh, it hurts so much.

677
00:52:51,829 --> 00:52:53,081
Oh, dear.

678
00:52:58,378 --> 00:53:01,339
That's definitely not an act. My goodness.

679
00:53:05,760 --> 00:53:07,554
That darn scumbag.

680
00:53:26,489 --> 00:53:30,034
- This woman.
- That's Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

681
00:53:30,535 --> 00:53:33,955
I think Yoo must have botched the job.

682
00:53:41,337 --> 00:53:43,130
Gosh, but still...

683
00:53:43,131 --> 00:53:44,756
A Chinese restaurant owner,
a convenience store owner

684
00:53:44,757 --> 00:53:46,466
and an office worker.

685
00:53:46,467 --> 00:53:48,885
They may look like nobodies on the outside

686
00:53:48,886 --> 00:53:51,096
but there's something
suspiciously professional

687
00:53:51,097 --> 00:53:52,723
about the way they operate.

688
00:53:52,724 --> 00:53:55,142
I mean, starting from
when they hit Capital

689
00:53:55,143 --> 00:53:57,519
and then the whole thing with
ruining President Yoo's drug shipment.

690
00:53:57,520 --> 00:53:59,479
Seriously, what's their motive?

691
00:53:59,480 --> 00:54:02,899
Why do they keep interfering
with our business at every turn?

692
00:54:02,900 --> 00:54:05,236
I just don't get it.

693
00:54:06,779 --> 00:54:08,071
By any chance

694
00:54:08,072 --> 00:54:11,366
I was just wondering
if you might have any hunches, sir.

695
00:54:11,367 --> 00:54:13,453
Chairman Do, you must have
a lot of time on your hands.

696
00:54:14,120 --> 00:54:15,413
Pardon?

697
00:54:16,831 --> 00:54:19,083
Worrying about such useless things.

698
00:54:20,543 --> 00:54:23,670
Oh, no, sir. Of course not.

699
00:54:23,671 --> 00:54:26,341
With preparing
for the Yeongseon Island Project

700
00:54:26,716 --> 00:54:28,468
I'm already stretched thin as it is.

701
00:54:29,552 --> 00:54:31,470
Right, so I'll just stop looking into this

702
00:54:31,471 --> 00:54:34,474
- and I'll wrap it up on my end.
- No, wait a minute.

703
00:54:35,516 --> 00:54:36,934
There's something I need to check.

704
00:54:38,895 --> 00:54:40,146
Understood.

705
00:54:41,564 --> 00:54:43,399
The owner of a Chinese restaurant.

706
00:54:46,069 --> 00:54:48,279
He's really moved up in the world.

707
00:54:54,410 --> 00:54:58,081
I'm heading back to my office.
I've got work to do.

708
00:54:58,706 --> 00:55:01,459
Prosecutor, I know
it's not my place to say

709
00:55:02,752 --> 00:55:05,213
but are you sure you should be
getting involved in this?

710
00:55:05,713 --> 00:55:08,758
Han Gyeong-wook has connections
in the Prosecutors' Office too.

711
00:55:09,342 --> 00:55:11,427
You could face pressure
from unexpected places.

712
00:55:12,136 --> 00:55:15,806
I came all the way to Yeongseon Island
and even had my life threatened.

713
00:55:15,807 --> 00:55:18,058
I even found out exactly
what those jerks are really like.

714
00:55:18,059 --> 00:55:20,353
You think I'm going to back down
over a little pressure?

715
00:55:21,062 --> 00:55:22,562
I'll risk my career to expose everything

716
00:55:22,563 --> 00:55:26,234
Han Gyeong-wook has done
and plans to do in the future.

717
00:55:27,026 --> 00:55:28,611
I will make him pay for his crimes.

718
00:55:30,071 --> 00:55:33,156
- What about Chairman Hwang's case?
- Right. I need to figure out

719
00:55:33,157 --> 00:55:35,451
how to properly reinvestigate
that case as well.

720
00:55:36,953 --> 00:55:39,080
- Thank you, Prosecutor.
- Of course.

721
00:55:40,998 --> 00:55:43,501
Hey. Can I talk to you?

722
00:55:44,252 --> 00:55:45,253
What?

723
00:55:54,053 --> 00:55:55,805
Well...

724
00:55:57,014 --> 00:55:59,850
About the hit-and-run driver
who hit you...

725
00:55:59,851 --> 00:56:02,478
I will catch them no matter what,
so don't you worry.

726
00:56:03,521 --> 00:56:05,272
Oh, okay.

727
00:56:05,273 --> 00:56:06,982
Is that what you wanted to talk about?

728
00:56:06,983 --> 00:56:08,735
Yes, that's part of it.

729
00:56:10,069 --> 00:56:14,781
I realized I never got the chance
to properly thank you.

730
00:56:14,782 --> 00:56:17,952
- Thank me for what?
- You saved my life. Twice.

731
00:56:18,661 --> 00:56:21,538
- I'm truly grateful.
- Oh, it was nothing.

732
00:56:21,539 --> 00:56:24,000
As long as you're okay, Prosecutor,
that's all that matters.

733
00:56:26,169 --> 00:56:27,587
I think you're a really good person.

734
00:56:28,296 --> 00:56:29,297
Me?

735
00:56:32,550 --> 00:56:34,385
The Bong Je-sun I've seen

736
00:56:36,554 --> 00:56:39,474
is someone who truly looks out for others.

737
00:56:40,558 --> 00:56:41,893
A good person.

738
00:56:43,853 --> 00:56:47,774
Even if you happen to go back
to your old self

739
00:56:49,817 --> 00:56:52,445
my gratitude toward you will never change.

740
00:56:56,532 --> 00:57:00,286
- Let me see your phone for a second.
- Oh, my phone?

741
00:57:14,342 --> 00:57:15,842
It's my number.

742
00:57:15,843 --> 00:57:18,179
It's not my work number.
It's my personal one.

743
00:57:18,596 --> 00:57:22,225
I don't give this number to anyone,
but I'm making an exception for you.

744
00:57:22,350 --> 00:57:24,685
But why are you giving this to me...

745
00:57:24,977 --> 00:57:26,646
Because I owe you.

746
00:57:27,730 --> 00:57:32,443
Save that number,
and call me if you ever need my help.

747
00:57:33,778 --> 00:57:37,406
Anytime. For anything. Just once.

748
00:57:37,657 --> 00:57:39,700
I'll help you out, no questions asked.

749
00:57:54,423 --> 00:57:57,760
Are you really going to keep him around?

750
00:57:58,052 --> 00:57:59,678
Why? You have a problem with it?

751
00:57:59,679 --> 00:58:02,848
No. To me, it seemed like
he really didn't remember anything.

752
00:58:02,849 --> 00:58:05,433
So I'm just wondering
if we really need to keep him with us.

753
00:58:05,434 --> 00:58:07,227
He also said he can't control
when his skills come back, right?

754
00:58:07,228 --> 00:58:08,311
Then he's just dead weight.

755
00:58:08,312 --> 00:58:11,649
Don't tell me you actually believe
Bulgae lost his memory.

756
00:58:13,317 --> 00:58:14,610
Don't you?

757
00:58:19,949 --> 00:58:23,578
Look. This is the CCTV footage
from near the hospital Gong-bok sent over.

758
00:58:24,412 --> 00:58:26,330
He said he went out
for chicken soup earlier, right?

759
00:58:26,455 --> 00:58:28,582
But there's a chicken soup place
right in front of the hospital.

760
00:58:28,583 --> 00:58:30,084
Why would he need to take a cab to go out?

761
00:58:32,211 --> 00:58:34,714
Maybe he just went to find
a better chicken soup place or something.

762
00:58:36,007 --> 00:58:38,467
That's ridiculous. Hey!

763
00:58:40,303 --> 00:58:42,971
He took a taxi to escape
and then decided to come back.

764
00:58:42,972 --> 00:58:45,349
Then he just shows up out of nowhere
saying he wants to help us?

765
00:58:45,975 --> 00:58:48,603
He's definitely up to something.

766
00:58:49,020 --> 00:58:50,479
But he seemed pretty clueless.

767
00:58:50,605 --> 00:58:52,272
You really think he could plan all this?

768
00:58:52,273 --> 00:58:55,276
He's Bulgae, not Bong Jae-sun.

769
00:58:55,484 --> 00:58:58,069
The master of disguise, Bulgae,
who can even change his voice.

770
00:58:58,070 --> 00:59:01,197
He's the kind of guy who'll stop
at nothing to complete his mission.

771
00:59:01,198 --> 00:59:03,074
Did you forget ten years ago
when he showed up

772
00:59:03,075 --> 00:59:04,577
on that ferry dressed as a woman?

773
00:59:05,870 --> 00:59:08,288
Him, acting all innocent
like this right now...

774
00:59:08,289 --> 00:59:09,539
It's nothing for a guy like him.

775
00:59:09,540 --> 00:59:12,083
So don't you let your guard down either.

776
00:59:12,084 --> 00:59:13,793
Okay, then if you knew
all that about Bulgae

777
00:59:13,794 --> 00:59:15,670
why did you agree to take him in?

778
00:59:15,671 --> 00:59:18,840
Mi-kyung and your wife
are at that K-Pop place or something.

779
00:59:18,841 --> 00:59:21,469
What if he shows his true colors
and does something to them?

780
00:59:21,928 --> 00:59:24,429
It would be better to just
get rid of him right now.

781
00:59:24,430 --> 00:59:26,848
Didn't you see
Prosecutor Gang's reaction earlier?

782
00:59:26,849 --> 00:59:28,808
Besides, everyone else
is completely convinced

783
00:59:28,809 --> 00:59:31,269
he's the naive Bong Je-sun.

784
00:59:31,270 --> 00:59:33,104
And he's putting on such a convincing act

785
00:59:33,105 --> 00:59:35,523
so it's useless for me
to go around saying he's Bulgae.

786
00:59:35,524 --> 00:59:37,651
It's better if I keep him close
and watch him.

787
00:59:37,652 --> 00:59:39,694
That way, we can figure out
what he's after.

788
00:59:39,695 --> 00:59:42,364
And then we can use it against him.

789
00:59:42,365 --> 00:59:45,034
So you keep your eyes peeled
and watch him closely.

790
00:59:46,494 --> 00:59:48,788
- He's coming.
- So he is, that jerk.

791
00:59:50,623 --> 00:59:52,874
Oh, sorry about that.
I got caught up talking.

792
00:59:52,875 --> 00:59:55,211
At least you know that. You drive.

793
00:59:58,923 --> 01:00:00,925
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

794
01:00:03,594 --> 01:00:06,846
- Nam-il.
- Oh, Uncle!

795
01:00:06,847 --> 01:00:08,557
Are you okay, Uncle?

796
01:00:10,685 --> 01:00:11,936
What happened?

797
01:00:12,228 --> 01:00:13,604
Are you allowed to leave
the hospital already?

798
01:00:14,689 --> 01:00:18,274
- I'm much better now. I'm fine.
- I know, but still.

799
01:00:18,275 --> 01:00:20,152
It's not like you're the Hulk. Jeez.

800
01:00:25,282 --> 01:00:27,326
Who... who are they?

801
01:00:28,494 --> 01:00:30,121
They're just some people I know.

802
01:00:30,871 --> 01:00:33,416
- Why are you alone? Where's everyone?
- What?

803
01:00:34,041 --> 01:00:37,753
The lady from the Chinese restaurant
came by with her kid earlier.

804
01:00:39,755 --> 01:00:44,217
- Daddy!
- Oh, Ji-woo, you're here.

805
01:00:44,218 --> 01:00:45,761
You came?

806
01:00:49,557 --> 01:00:52,685
- Thank you.
- I still don't trust you 100%.

807
01:00:52,977 --> 01:00:55,521
I only came because of Ji-woo,
so don't get the wrong idea.

808
01:00:56,272 --> 01:00:57,647
I know.

809
01:00:57,648 --> 01:00:58,941
You did well.

810
01:00:59,942 --> 01:01:02,236
But where's your father?

811
01:01:02,945 --> 01:01:05,947
I don't know. He said he was going
to close up the shop and come

812
01:01:05,948 --> 01:01:07,949
but then he said
a large group of customers showed up

813
01:01:07,950 --> 01:01:09,034
so he isn't coming.

814
01:01:09,035 --> 01:01:11,120
Still, you should have
brought him with you.

815
01:01:11,245 --> 01:01:13,164
He said he wouldn't come.
What was I supposed to do?

816
01:01:13,706 --> 01:01:17,250
My dad's mad because of you,
so you go deal with him yourself.

817
01:01:17,251 --> 01:01:19,086
Jeez.

818
01:01:20,087 --> 01:01:22,339
All right. I'll go get him.

819
01:01:22,965 --> 01:01:25,009
- Ji-woo, stay here for a minute.
- Okay.

820
01:01:26,427 --> 01:01:29,346
You explain the situation to people
when they get here.

821
01:01:29,972 --> 01:01:31,015
And...

822
01:01:36,395 --> 01:01:39,482
- Keep a close eye on Bulgae.
- Yes, got it.

823
01:01:44,528 --> 01:01:46,614
IMCHEON DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

824
01:01:59,293 --> 01:02:03,046
Prosecutor Gang? Long time no see.

825
01:02:03,047 --> 01:02:05,466
Are you back from your leave today?

826
01:02:06,550 --> 01:02:07,968
I'm sorry, Chief Prosecutor.

827
01:02:09,095 --> 01:02:10,638
I'm sorry I didn't answer your calls

828
01:02:11,013 --> 01:02:14,140
and missed my return date.
I truly have no excuse.

829
01:02:14,141 --> 01:02:17,269
Hey, that's not like you.
No need to apologize.

830
01:02:18,521 --> 01:02:20,523
Judging by how well you look

831
01:02:20,898 --> 01:02:23,066
you must have had a good time off.

832
01:02:23,067 --> 01:02:26,904
I am so sorry. I'll accept any punishment.

833
01:02:30,533 --> 01:02:31,826
You can go.

834
01:02:32,576 --> 01:02:35,246
- Sir?
- Isn't your return report finished?

835
01:02:35,746 --> 01:02:37,873
- I said, you can go.
- But Mr. Kim said

836
01:02:38,415 --> 01:02:40,291
that you were desperately looking for me.

837
01:02:40,292 --> 01:02:43,712
That was then, and this is now.

838
01:02:44,755 --> 01:02:46,715
Or what? You want to stay
and write a formal apology?

839
01:02:46,841 --> 01:02:49,134
No, sir. Really.

840
01:02:49,135 --> 01:02:52,471
I'm so sorry.
Thank you so much. Take care, sir.

841
01:03:06,402 --> 01:03:07,570
Yes.

842
01:03:07,862 --> 01:03:10,823
Just as you said,
Gang Yeong-ae came to work.

843
01:03:11,574 --> 01:03:13,450
I'll put my people on her.

844
01:03:13,909 --> 01:03:16,787
We won't lose her like last time.

845
01:03:23,794 --> 01:03:26,588
Hey, why are you here?
O-ran's already there.

846
01:03:26,589 --> 01:03:28,965
I told you yesterday.
It's dangerous right now.

847
01:03:28,966 --> 01:03:31,218
You need to close
the restaurant for a while.

848
01:03:31,927 --> 01:03:33,303
You said you understood yesterday.

849
01:03:33,304 --> 01:03:36,514
I said I'd convince O-ran.
When did I say I would leave?

850
01:03:36,515 --> 01:03:39,476
And who are you
to decide to close the business?

851
01:03:40,561 --> 01:03:43,480
Come on, you've been wanting a break.
Just think of this as a vacation.

852
01:03:43,606 --> 01:03:46,358
But how can I think of it as a vacation
when it's not?

853
01:03:46,483 --> 01:03:49,110
To you, this may just be a restaurant
you worked at reluctantly

854
01:03:49,111 --> 01:03:53,531
but O-ran's mother and I
poured our youth into building this place.

855
01:03:53,532 --> 01:03:57,577
Does it make any sense to close down
because of some thugs?

856
01:03:57,578 --> 01:04:00,831
- Father.
- You go and take care of O-ran.

857
01:04:01,373 --> 01:04:04,919
I can handle this restaurant
just fine on my own.

858
01:04:15,012 --> 01:04:18,015
Go on upstairs and get some rest.
I'll close up.

859
01:04:19,016 --> 01:04:21,268
I haven't been able to come
to the restaurant much lately.

860
01:04:22,436 --> 01:04:23,604
All right, then.

861
01:04:24,355 --> 01:04:26,190
Finish up and come upstairs.

862
01:04:43,290 --> 01:04:44,708
We're closed.

863
01:05:17,658 --> 01:05:19,493
Long time no see, Ho-myeong.

864
01:05:26,834 --> 01:05:29,378
SPECIAL THANKS
TO KIM SANG-KYUNG AND KWON YUL

865
01:05:44,143 --> 01:05:45,226
Do you and everyone around you

866
01:05:45,227 --> 01:05:47,228
have to be destroyed
before you learn your lesson?

867
01:05:47,229 --> 01:05:48,730
Is it okay for you to go up
against someone that dangerous?

868
01:05:48,731 --> 01:05:52,608
- Take care of that woman.
- I'll have to get some blood on my hands.

869
01:05:52,609 --> 01:05:54,319
That USB drive
with Han Gyeong-wook's weakness.

870
01:05:54,320 --> 01:05:56,571
It means that the package has surfaced.

871
01:05:56,572 --> 01:05:59,824
Those two have the missing package.

872
01:05:59,825 --> 01:06:02,076
We just have to make Bulgae talk
and get the package.

873
01:06:02,077 --> 01:06:03,620
Agent Bulgae of the Ministry
of People's Armed Forces.

874
01:06:03,746 --> 01:06:05,288
A human weapon trained in North Korea.

875
01:06:05,289 --> 01:06:06,873
- What?
- What?

876
01:06:06,874 --> 01:06:07,957
I think you've got it wrong.

877
01:06:07,958 --> 01:06:10,043
I'm telling you,
I really don't remember a thing.

878
01:06:10,044 --> 01:06:12,045
He says he can't remember anything.
How are you supposed to make him talk?

879
01:06:12,046 --> 01:06:13,047
Tie him up.

880
01:06:13,797 --> 01:06:15,549
- You've really gone too far.
- Stop.

881
01:06:15,674 --> 01:06:18,217
- Everyone will be in danger.
- We're not far from the finish line.

882
01:06:18,218 --> 01:06:19,302
We need to strike first.

883
01:06:19,303 --> 01:06:21,555
Hey, Bulgae. Now make your choice.
